HEADWORD: Self-elective
<hw>Self`-e*lect"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the
right of electing one's self, or, as a body, of electing its own
members.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

